body_html: The AOT generated binary contains machine code for the CPU you're targeting (for instance x86) whereas the TF graph is a serialized representation of the TensorFlow graph (very different from machine code). Everything else remaining equal, you can expect that a larger TF graph will generate a larger binary; but other than that there is no correlation between these two things.
